Here's an advanced find command you can run to find files over 10 MB (no variables in this one, just copy and paste):
find / -mount -noleaf -type f -size +10000k -print0 | xargs -0 ls -lhSr | awk '{printf "%*s %s\n",7,$5":",$9}'
